# Azure Server Setup Notes

## Project Overview

This project involved creating a cloud-hosted Cybersecurity Awareness website using Microsoft Azure Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS).

## Virtual Machine Configuration

Platform: Microsoft Azure

Operating System: Ubuntu Linux 24.04 LTS

Web Server: Apache2

Public IP Address: 20.70.146.68

## Virtual Machine Creation

1. Logged into Microsoft Azure Portal. 
2. Created a new Virtual Machine. 
3. Selected Ubuntu 24.04 LTS image.
4. Chose standard B1s size. 
5. Enabled SSH authentication.
6. Created and downloaded SSH key pair.
7. Deployed the virtual machine. 

## SSH Access

connected remotley using macOS Terminal.

Example command:

ssh -i azurekey2026.pem azureuser@20.70.146.68

## Network Security

The following inbound rules were enabled:

- Port 22 (SSH) for remote administration 
- Port 80 (HTTP) for website access

These rules were configured through the Azure Network Security Group associated with the virtual machine. 

## Apache Installation

Updated the server:

sudo apt update

Installed Apache:

sudo apt install apache2 -y

Verified Apache service:

sudo systemct1 status apache2

## Website Deployment

Website files were stored in:

/var/www/html

The index.html file was edited to create the Cybersecurity Awareness Website.

## DNS Configuration

Configured an Azure DNS label through the public IP resource.

The DNS hostname was linked to the virtual machine's public IP address.

## Custom Script

A custom Bash script name serverinfo.sh was developed to automate server monitoring tasks.

The script generates a Cyber Awareness Server Status Report and displays:

- Server hostname
- Current date and time
- System uptime
- Disk space usage
- Memory usage

Execution:

./serverinfo.sh

The script reduces the need to manually enter multiple Linux commands and provides a quick overview of server health and resource utilisation. 

## Testing and Verification

The server was tested to ensure all components functioned correctly.

Verification included:

- Successful SSH connection from macOS Terminal
- Apache web server running correctly 
- Website accessible through public IP address
- Website accessible through Azure DNS hostname
- Custom Bash script executed successfully

